    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>CADBURY SEEKS KRAFT CANDY UNIT</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Andrew Ross Sorkin</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Sorkin, Andrew Ross</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Cadbury Schweppes is in talks to acquire French candy and chewing gum business of Kraft; financial terms undisclosed (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The candy and beverage company Cadbury Schweppes said it was in talks to acquire the French candy and chewing gum business of Kraft, a unit of the Philip Morris Companies. Cadbury Schweppes, based in Britain, refused to disclose how much it might pay. Analysts expect the unit, which makes the Hollywood gum and Krema candy brands, could fetch as much as $450 million.</p>
        <p>Andrew Ross Sorkin (NYT)</p>
      </block>
